The paper focuses on change impact analysis in software engineering, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed algorithm, LCIP, is a learning algorithm, indicating a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) subfield. The paper also deals with object-oriented software, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The simulation of changes through code mutations suggests a potential fit for software development (cs.SD). Finally, the use of past impacts to predict future impacts suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
